ralia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: \\\"Well, the women just finishing up.\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 535, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You know what women are like\\u2026 hanging around, doing their make-up.\\\"\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 603, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ballard's co-commentator, Lizzie Simmonds, described the remark as 'outrageous'.\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 685, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 605, \"end\": 612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999931212303301, \"rank\": 6.873859259158551e-06, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eurosport have since removed Ballard from their coverage of the 2024 Games and released an official statement.\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 715, \"end\": 722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.9999931212303301, \"rank\": 6.873859259158551e-06, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It read: \\\"During a segment of Eurosport's coverage last night, commentator Bob Ballard made an inappropriate comment.\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 915, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 873, \"end\": 876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\", \"score\": 0.9956177558196261, \"rank\": 0.004016028260058722, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\"}, {\"begin\": 87